sequenceDiagram
    participant Deployer as deploy.sh Container<br/>(UBI8-minimal)
    participant K8sAPI as OpenShift API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Operator as ODH Operator<br/>(KfDef Controller)
    participant Manifests as odh-manifests<br/>tarball (file://)
    participant Prometheus as Prometheus<br/>9090/TCP
    participant ClusterProm as Cluster Prometheus<br/>openshift-monitoring<br/>9091/TCP HTTPS
    participant Components as Platform Components<br/>(Dashboard, NBC, ModelMesh,<br/>DSPO, Model Controller)
    participant Blackbox as Blackbox Exporter<br/>9114/TCP HTTPS
    participant Alertmanager as Alertmanager<br/>9093/TCP
    participant PagerDuty as PagerDuty API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant DMS as Dead Man's Snitch<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant SMTP as SMTP Server<br/>STARTTLS

    Note over Deployer,K8sAPI: Flow 1: Platform Deployment

    Deployer->>K8sAPI: Create namespaces (oc apply)<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token<br/>TLS 1.2+
    Deployer->>K8sAPI: Apply KfDef CRs to<br/>redhat-ods-applications<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: KfDef CR watch notification
    Operator->>Manifests: Load component manifests<br/>file:// protocol
    Manifests-->>Operator: YAML manifests
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create component Deployments<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token<br/>TLS 1.2+
    Deployer->>K8sAPI: Apply monitoring, network policies,<br/>dashboard CRDs, ISV tiles<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token

    Note over Prometheus,Components: Flow 2: Prometheus Metrics Federation

    Prometheus->>ClusterProm: Federate metrics<br/>9091/TCP HTTPS<br/>TLS (service CA)<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (SA)
    Prometheus->>Components: Scrape /metrics<br/>8080/TCP HTTP<br/>No Encryption<br/>No Auth
    Prometheus->>Blackbox: Scrape probes<br/>9114/TCP HTTPS<br/>TLS<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    Blackbox->>Components: Probe user-facing endpoints<br/>Various ports HTTPS/HTTP<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (SA)

    Note over Prometheus,SMTP: Flow 3: Alert Notification (Managed Service)

    Prometheus->>Alertmanager: Fire alert rules<br/>9093/TCP HTTP<br/>localhost (no encryption)
    Alertmanager->>PagerDuty: Critical alert notification<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: Service Key
    Alertmanager->>SMTP: Email notification<br/>STARTTLS<br/>Auth: Username/Password
    Alertmanager->>DMS: Watchdog heartbeat<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: URL Token
